  static const String waterDescription =
      " The exploitation of environmental elements – air, soil and water – as natural resources is as old as the history of mankind. They wanted to tame them, but at the same time they were afraid of them, because e.g. windstorms, earthquakes and floods – as certain forms of environmental elements – had a devastating effect on them. Conquest required experience, experience became knowledge, and knowledge was passed on to the next generation.The nature of the material world was already preoccupying the man of antiquity, from which he drew his conclusions through observation. Archimedes created his law of buoyancy, Heraclitus‘ famous saying was also born in antiquity: “Pantha rhei – Everything flows. The only constant is change itself.” The initial seeds of atomic theory can already be found in the works of ancient Greek thinkers. First, they imagined four primordial elements (fire, water, earth and air), then Democritus spoke of several identical atoms (=indivisible in Greek).The primal elements also appear in astrology, which express the basic energies of our lives. Water flows, almost unstoppably, and this perfectly exemplifies people with a water sign – especially when it comes to their emotions.And in 2024, science is already there, as researchers have for the first time witnessed the formation of tiny water bubbles in real time, which they also captured on video.";

